HEADWORD: Superinduce
<hw>Su`per*in*duce"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Superinduced</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Superinducing</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>super-</ets> +
<ets>induce</ets>: cf. L. <ets>superinducere</ets> to draw over.]</ety>
<def>To bring in, or upon, as an addition to something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Long custom of sinning <qex>superinduces</qex> upon the soul new
and absurd desires.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superinducement</ent>⟦br⟧
